title: How have waiting times after an urgent referral changed?, font-size: 20%
analysis_commentary: The percentage of people being seen within two weeks remained largely consistent, between 95% and 96% from Q3 2009/10 onwards. However, in Q3 2013/14, it decreased, reaching an all-time low of 93.5% in Q1 2014/15. It has since increased again to 94.7% but in Q2 2015/16 dipped to 93.5%.
